  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 28 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 15 critical, 7 high, 7 medium, 10 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), London Gatwick (LGW/EGKK) and Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR); plus 19 other bases. 7 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is snow-related runway contamination risk, mist and low cloud base  — most notably around Copernicus Wrocław (WRO/EPWR), Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT) and Belgrade Nikola Tesla (BEG/LYBE). Network hotspots: Berlin Brandenburg Willy Brandt (BER/EDDB), Hamburg Helmut Schmidt (HAM/EDDH), Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), Maastricht Aachen (MST/EHBK), Kraków John Paul II (KRK/EPKK) and 23 others. Primary drivers: snow / blowing snow, low cloud base and mist. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Hamburg Helmut Schmidt (HAM/EDDH), Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), Maastricht Aachen (MST/EHBK) and 9 others.",
